From 1875c8d8dff56babdc487b1f217bff431df06543 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AAP Rebuild <aap-rebuild-bot@localhost>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 16:21:08 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] patch: EDA automation_server_url uses _controller_name + FQDN
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Original: 'http://{{ ansible_operator_meta.name }}-controller-service'

Two compounding problems:
  1. Bare hostname (no namespace) — fragile cross-namespace.
  2. Hardcodes service name as <aap-name>-controller-service, which only
     resolves when controller CR is named '<aap-name>-controller'. If
     spec.controller.name overrides the default (we use 'ap-controller'
     against an AAP CR named 'aap'), awx-operator emits
     <controller-name>-service = 'ap-controller-service', NOT
     'aap-controller-service'. EDA -> controller calls then fail DNS.

Fix: derive from _controller_name (set by combine_controller_defaults)
with a fallback to <aap-name>-controller for the default-name case.
Append namespace + svc.cluster.local for FQDN.

  http://<_controller_name>-service.<namespace>.svc.cluster.local

User can still override via spec.eda.automation_server_url (combine_eda
merges spec.eda over _default_eda, so explicit wins).

Mirrors the gateway-side fix in patch 0003 (controller_api_url 3-tier
resolution) — same root cause, same FQDN-based service-name pattern.
---
 roles/ansibleautomationplatform/vars/main.yml | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/roles/ansibleautomationplatform/vars/main.yml b/roles/ansibleautomationplatform/vars/main.yml
index 32faf5b..393ab7e 100644
--- a/roles/ansibleautomationplatform/vars/main.yml
+++ b/roles/ansibleautomationplatform/vars/main.yml
@@ -103,7 +103,7 @@ _default_eda:
   no_log: "{{ no_log }}"
   idle_deployment: false
   postgres_configuration_secret: "{{ eda_pg_config['resources'][0]['metadata']['name'] }}"
-  automation_server_url: 'http://{{ ansible_operator_meta.name }}-controller-service'
+  automation_server_url: 'http://{{ _controller_name | default(ansible_operator_meta.name + "-controller") }}-service.{{ ansible_operator_meta.namespace }}.svc.cluster.local'
   ui_disabled: true
   public_base_url: '{{ gateway_url }}'
   event_stream:
